* Breath rasped in her lungs, snorting to clear them of the scent of the ash 
as her keen eye-sight penitrated the clouds that surrounded the field.
Her head had snepped towards the direction of a roar seconds after hears her 
left her throat, trying to see as far as she could and only mannaging to see 
a...feathery outline?
But her thoughts told her who it was.
< Prowl....>
* Her logicle mind controled this mode, but the wild sense was still there 
and was eager to get into the fight.
There was a slight flash of light in the ash before she heard a voice boom 
over the clashes of metal against metal and yells of angry bots.
She snarled/roared when a stray shot sent from Menasor landed a few feet 
away from her, sending dirt flying towards her face.
Growling she backed away and then began to move towards his position, 
glancing towards Prowls direction as she moved.
She'd decided on a target.
Since she really didn't want to use speech right now she roared, waiting for 
a reply from him.
It was clear communications, explainign that a gustalt such as Menasor could 
be taken by them IF they moved together and in one songle unit.
It was time to get to work.*
